course.subject: FINA
course.name: Doctoral Seminar: Empirical Corporate Finance
course.description: This course covers major topics in empirical corporate finance. A large part of this course is devoted to examining research questions in capital structure, corporate investments, and corporate governance. The focus is on the more recent literature in these broad areas of corporate finance. The goal of the course is to help students get ready for doing their own research.
course.prerequisites: FINA 790I prior to 2011-12; FINA 7900A from 2011-12
